Package com.undercamber

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CompletionCallback
    Callback to notify listeners of test completion.
    ConfigurationCallback
    Called by Undercamber to configure the test system.
    Requirement
    Interface for a Requirement
    TestUnit
    A functional interface for TestManager.addSubtest(com.undercamber.TestUnit)
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Configurator
    This class configures a test system in Undercamber.
    Path
    A convenience class to build path-like strings in a platform-independent way.
    Prerequisite
    This indicates to Undercamber what tests must run and pass before another test can run.
    SimpleRequirement
    A bare-bones implementation of Requirement
    StringExpander
    A convenience class.
    Tag
    Used to create pre-defined groups of tests.
    TestData
    Indicates the results of a single test
    TestManager
    The primary interface between Undercamber and one test.
    TestSetBuilder
    Configure a test set.
    Undercamber
    Main class
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    OperatingSystem
    A convenience enum for discovering what operating system is running.
    Prerequisite.IncludeSubtests
    Indicates whether the Prerequisite's subtests should also be considered prerequisites
    Prerequisite.PrerequisiteMatchMultiplicity
    Indicates how to handle identical prerequisites
    Prerequisite.Type
    Indicates to Undercamber the type of the prerequisite.

    This conditional types are needed for report generation when determining which tests do not contribute to a requirement.
    SubtestContinuationMode
    Indicates haw to handle subtests when a parent test fails.
    SubtestSequencingMode
    Indicates how subtests should be sequenced
    TestState
    Indicates the stage in a test's lifecycle.
    ValidationLevel
    Indicates validation level
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InternalException
    This exception indicates an exception internal to Undercamber™.
    UserError
    This exception indicates a user error detected by Undercamber™.
